frameDefinitions: A Cause triggers a System to operate in accordance with its intended purpose.
This frame describes either the creation of a Flame by a Kindler or non-sentient Cause, or the igniting of Flammables by a Kindler or a Cause.
An Agent initiates the beginning of an ongoing Activity in which he will be continuously involved. '' 'At the same time, city-states began to grow in influence on the southern Greek mainland.'
An Agent acts to begin the life of a Process.
frameExamples: Smoking a cigarette will normally not <t>set off</t> a smoke alarm.
Taliban militants recently <t>set fire</t> to several schools.
At the same time, city-states <t>began</t> to grow in influence on the southern Greek mainland.
After discovering her knack for organization, she decided to try to  <t>launch</t> a career in human resources.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Cause</fen> interacts with the <fen>System</fen> such that conditions are met for the <fen>System</fen> to operate.
The <fen>System</fen> interacts with or detects the <fen>Cause</fen> and activates.
An entity which participates in a <fen>Cause</fen>, perhaps volitionally and perhaps not.
The time when the triggering takes place.
Where the triggering takes place.
The <fen>Kindler</fen> is the person performing the intentional act.
The <fen>Flame</fen> is what is created by the Kindler.
The Flamables is the the object that is set on fire by the Kindler.
The cause of the fire.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the event occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the event takes place.
This role identifies the <fen>Activity</fen> that an <fen>Agent</fen> starts.
This role identifies the being that starts the intentional <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> starts an <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Agent</fen> starts an <fen>Activity</fen>.
This Frame Element marks expressions that indicate the process that the <fen>Agent</fen> initiates.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the actor responsible for starting the <fen>Process</fen>.
This role is for the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> initiates the <fen>Process</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Process</fen> is initiated.
A force, process, or event that produces an effect.
Agents in a joint or reciprocal action (e.g. exchange)
A positive or negative evaluation of the Phenomenon.
An entity which participates in a <fen>Cause</fen>, perhaps volitionally and perhaps not.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
listRoleExamples: <fex>His presence</fex> set off the motion alarms.
They let him through even though something triggered <fex>the metal detector</fex>?
<fex>She</fex> set off the silent alarm before being shoved into the middle of the lobby.
Three bombs were set off <fex>at three o'clock today</fex>.
Police came running downstairs when someone set off the metal detector <fex>at the county courthouse</fex>.
<fex>Mark</fex> started the fire with a magnifying glass.
<fex>That one stone</fex>, apparently, caused the avalanche that engulfed square miles of forest.
